MTF, Tom, Cook, SW,<br><br>
Brothers of Choice,<br><br>
Thanks for your words of friendship, advice and encouragement. I flamed out yesterday, really bad. I went down and bounced along the bottom. I was back in a place I would sooner forget but that I have to acknowledge is really an indellible part of me. No one was home when it hit, so I came here and opened up. That really helped. People unfamiliar with this PTSD affliction can read between the lines of my post and sense some of what was going on in my head. It does not bother me to do this. Part of the process of controlling it is admitting and understanding you have it to begin with!<br><br>
I pulled myself up and out and I am now sitting on the edge of the foxhole. In a while I'll be headed off to the C ration pile with the rest of you! The peach cobbler is MINE! HA! <br><br>
MTF, you posted elsewhere about my display of anger vs. introspection. You are right that I am heavy into introspection right now. It is necessary to control the rage that is just below the surface. There is a big difference between anger and rage. I am actually still learning about anger. I am actually practicing it! I think I did a good job with our friend! Just one more step along the way. By the way, I really would like to see a scalp dance! Were you kidding, or is there really such a thing in your tradition? I could probably learn from it!<br><br>
Cook, I now know I am not alone in some of those feelings that are sometimes hard to get out because most just would not understand.<br><br>
Tom, your words are always an anchor for me. Somehow you have the knack of balance. Thanks!<br><br>
SW, you old critter. I can talk to you this way because I know you too well. Thanks for the secret decoder ring phone #. It's in my wallet!<br><br>
Your Brother of Choice,<br><br>
Art<br><br>

